    section
        p.section-type.font-gilroy the challenge
        h2 efficiency is not the real problem
        p This is a redesigning of the web version of sign up form. Credible's current form follows most of the best practice of web form design (single column design, breaking down into 3 steps, labels on the top left, etc.) The current form is already pretty efficient, so in order to have more users finish the form, maybe efficiency is not the real problem.
        img.full-width(src="/assets/internship/challenge.png")

    //- research
    section.bg-shading
        p.section-type.font-gilroy understand users
        h2 people are afraid of forms
        p I took a step back and start to ask myself very basic questions like: Why people are not willing to finish the form? - Because I don't like forms. Why don't people like forms? - Because it reminds of tons of tedious paperwork. Below are the search results of word "form" on Google image. These forms are always very long, difficult to understand, requires you a lot of sensitive data. But most of our current web forms still use this kind of format (a rectangular field with labels on it), which will give users these bad feelings subconsciously.
        img.full-width(src="/assets/internship/understand-user.png")

    //- solutions
    section.bg-arrow
        p.section-type.font-gilroy solutions
        h2 What if we make the forms do not look like forms?
        p With the insight "People are afraid of form", I started to ask myself "What if we make the form not looks like a form?", so that users can overcome the mindset that they are filling the form and forget the subconscious uneasiness. So I came up with two concepts as below.
        
        h3 nature language input form
        p Natural language input form converts traditional web form into several uncompleted sentences. A whole sentence provide a humanity feel, comparing with rectangle input fields and labels.
        video(autoplay, loop, preload="auto")
            source(src="/assets/internship/NLF-video.mp4")

        h3 conversational UI
        p Using conversational UI creates a better emotional connection with users, which makes users feel like we are here to help them. On the other hand, navigating through different fields is painful on mobile and conversational form can solve this problem too. Though, it may not be an  efficient way to input data.
        video(autoplay, loop, preload="auto")
            source(src="/assets/internship/CF-video.mp4")

    //- next
    section.bg-shading
