        h2 internship highlights
        p Being in a really fast-paced start-up company, I got the chance to work on different types of projects. Below are some of the highlighted projects I've worked on during my internship.
        
        h3 Credible Mobile Navigation Redesign
        p The initial project was to add a new function on Credible's mobile offer dashboard, but the original design is not scalable. On page level, there are two full-width buttons as the entry point of two features. The original header already has two menus but some links within in the menu are not helpful for users, so we decide to rethink the whole mobile header and navigation system to help users navigate through the sites and use our new features easily. I went through several iterations and these are some key considerations:
        ul
            li Remove links that are not used frequently, based on data from Google Analytics
            li Group links to reduce users' cognitive load and reorder the links according to data
            li Improve the scalability to make sure adding new features in the further won't break user's experience
            li Explored and prototyped different transition and interaction of menu. 
        .flex-container
            .flex-item
